title: Reasashhsuahs
description:
Beneath the hush of silver skies,
Where morning’s breath begins to rise,
The world awakes in gentle light,
Soft shadows fading into flight.

The trees, once still, now start to sway,
Their branches stretch to greet the day.
A robin sings its waking tune,
A lullaby beneath the moon.

The dew upon the meadow's skin
Reflects the gold now seeping in.
Each blade of grass, a shining thread,
Woven where the night has fled.

The mountains wear a crown of mist,
By sunlight’s fingers gently kissed.
And rivers hum in whispered streams,
Like echoes born from fragile dreams.

The world, reborn with every sun,
Reminds us life has just begun.
So walk with hope, with open eyes,
Beneath these ever-changing skies.

For though the dusk will come again,
And stars will write their calm refrain,
There lies in every dawn’s embrace
A chance to find a sacred place.
